                                  CONTENTS

This software package consists of the following files:

Protector               - the program itself
Protector.info          - it`s icon

Protector_E.Guide       - english amigaguide doc
Protector_E.Guide.info  - it`s icon

Protector_D.Guide       - german amigaguide doc
Protector_D.Guide.info  - it`s icon

Libs/Shutdown.library   - the shutdown.library from Olaf Barthel.

@ENDNODE
===============================================================================
@NODE DESCRIPTION
                                  DESCRIPTION

        The Protector is able to prevent your BBS from beeing blocked by
                        Guru Meditations and Requesters.

            It requires @{"Kickstart 2.04" LINK COPYRIGHT}, @{"Workbench 2.0" LINK COPYRIGHT} or better.
               and the @{"shutdown.library" LINK SHUTDOWN}.

              The Protector contains an embedded version id in CBM
  format which can be shown using the Shell command VERSION of Workbench 2.0.

  All program components are tested with Enforcer V37.28 and MungWall V37.55.

@ENDNODE
===============================================================================
@NODE USAGE
                                    USAGE

  Simply put the Protector into the WBStartup drawer or start it from CLI.
   To remove it, start it again or remove it with the Commodities Exchange
                                   program.

 The CLI-arguments and tooltypes are:
 
 CX_POPUP/K                 - show the window on startup.
                              default: on.
 DISABLED/S                 - disable the protector on startup.
                              default: off. (Enabled)
 LOGFILE/K                  - filename for the log.
                              default: off ("")
 ENABLECMD/K                - command which will be executed on enabling.
                              default: Execute S:ProtectorEnableCMD.
 DISABLECMD/K               - command which will be executed on disabling.
                              default: Execute S:ProtectorDisableCMD.
 SHUTDOWNCMD/K              - command which will be executed on shutdown.
                              default: Execute S:ProtectorShutDownCMD.
 XPOS/N                     - x-position of the Protector-window.
                              default: 0.
 YPOS/N                     - y-position of the Protector-window.
                              default: under the titlebar.
 MAXEVENTS/N                - the maximum number of events (requester, alerts),
                              which are allowed to happen in 10 seconds.
                              default: off.
 REQDELAY/N                 - the time after that the requester will be can-
                              celed automaticaly.
                              default: off.
 RETRYMATCH/K               - if a requestertext starts with this string, the
                              requester will be retried, not canceled.
                              default: off

                                     DISABLED IN UNREGISTERED VERSION

 TRAPPATCH/S                - activates the patching of the Trap-Vectors. After
                              this the following exceptions are immediately
                              followed by a reset:

                                BusError
                                AddressError
                                IllegalInstruction
                                DivisionByZero

                              An entry in the log will _not_ be written.

                              Warning: The chance that this "feature" disturbes
                              the system more than making use is really big. I
                              suggest not to activate it.
                              default: off.

@ENDNODE
===============================================================================
@NODE FEATURES
                                  FEATURES

 - uses the @{"shutdown.library" LINK SHUTDOWN} for the reset.
 - easy removable cause it`s a commodity.
 - has an window with activation-button.
 - safe repatchroutines.
 - supports CLI-arguments and tooltypes.
 - is able to build up a logfile.
 - Windowposition is setable.
 - causes a shutdown, if more than a given number of requesters and
   alerts are coming up in 10 seconds.
 - is able to execute commands on enabling, disabling and shutdown.
 - cancels requesters after a defined time.
 - is able to retry defined requesters.

@ENDNODE
