@NODE HISTORY
                                   HISTORY
V1.0>

  - requester`s patched
  - alert`s patched
  - window for removing

V1.1> (19.03.93)

  - enhanced code
  - delay before reset

V1.2> (03.08.93)

  - changed to commodity
  - removed window

V1.3> (29.08.93)

  - added window with activation-button
  - added the CLI-args
  - added tooltypes

V1.4> (02.11.93)

  - added logfile.
  - changed reset to shutdown.

V1.5> (30.12.93)

  - added windowpositions.
  - added maxevents.
  - reworked logfileoutput.

V1.6> (01.03.93)

  - added EnableCMD and DisableCMD.
  - window is now fontsenitiv.
  - reworked the code a little bit.

V1.7> (03.05.94)

  - added ShutDownCMD.
  - added timed requesters.
  - reworked the code again.
  - removed the deadlocks caused by logfileproblems.
  - removed several small bugs in the logfileoutput.
  - the protector is now shareware.

V1.8> (22.03.95)

  - removed heavy bug in the repatch-routines.
  - added trappatch.
  - reworked logfileoutput.

V1.9> (06.05.95)

  - changed the easyrequestargs-function to work better with gfx-boards.
  - added retrymatch.

V2.0> (06.12.95)

  - fixed autorequest bug.
  - added patternmatching to retrymatch.

@ENDNODE
===============================================================================
@NODE BUGS
                                      BUGS

        The Protector has to be started _after_ tools like ARQ to work.

    You should choose a special partition for the log, because the risk that
   the system crashes during writing is much higher during a malfunction that
     causes an alert or requester. It should be possible for everybody to a
                        small extra partition for this!

            On my system, the "printer trouble" requester locks up.

@ENDNODE
